{
  "message": "fix: use qualified GT_ROLE patterns in rig-scoped role TOMLs\n\nRole TOML [env] sections had unqualified GT_ROLE values (e.g., \"witness\")\nthat could overwrite the canonical qualified values set by AgentEnv\n(e.g., \"gastown/witness\"). Now use {rig} pattern expansion so TOML\nvalues are correct even if applied standalone.\n\nDefense-in-depth (witness manager skipping already-set keys) was already\non main; this fixes the source data.\n\nCherry-picked from PR #2504 (GH#2492).\n\nCo-authored-by: Chris Deal <DreadPirateRobertz@users.noreply.github.com>\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
  "files": [
    {
      "sha": "6d950d9a80053e317f28077048894c84f0116905",
      "filename": "internal/config/roles/crew.toml",
      "status": "modified",
      "additions": 1,
      "deletions": 1,
      "changes": 2,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/gastownhall/gastown/blob/068b1dd8e5c4bacf5d99f4de2cf9712729f129f5/internal%2Fconfig%2Froles%2Fcrew.toml",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/gastownhall/gastown/raw/068b1dd8e5c4bacf5d99f4de2cf9712729f129f5/internal%2Fconfig%2Froles%2Fcrew.toml",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gastownhall/gastown/contents/internal%2Fconfig%2Froles%2Fcrew.toml?ref=068b1dd8e5c4bacf5d99f4de2cf9712729f129f5",
      "patch": "@@ -13,7 +13,7 @@ needs_pre_sync = true\n start_command = \"exec claude --dangerously-skip-permissions\"\n \n [env]\n-GT_ROLE = \"crew\"\n+GT_ROLE = \"{rig}/crew/{name}\"\n GT_SCOPE = \"rig\"\n \n [health]"
    },
    {
      "sha": "db8c6c64395f966f9fea3b52bef660007af0624d",
      "filename": "internal/config/roles/polecat.toml",
